programStages.name: Care at birth
programStages.description: Intrapartum care / Childbirth / Labour and delivery

programStages.name: Case investigation & classification
programStages.description: This includes the investigation of the index case (including the confirmation of symptoms, previous malaria history, LLIN usage details, IRS details), and the summary of the results for the case investigation including the final case classification (both the species type and the case classification).

programStages.name: Case outcome
programStages.description: This stage details the final outcome of the case

programStages.name: Diagnosis & treatment
programStages.description: This stage is used to identify initial diagnosis and treatment. This includes the method of case detection, information about the case include travel history, method of diagnosis, malaria species type and treatment details.

programStages.name: Foci investigation & classification
programStages.description: Includes the details on the foci investigation (including information on households, population, geography, breeding sites, species types, vector behaviour) as well as its final classification at the time of the investigation. This is a repeatable stage as foci can be investigated more than once and may change their classification as time goes on.

programStages.name: Foci response
programStages.description: Details the public health response conducted within the foci  (including diagnosis and treatment activities, vector control actions and the effectiveness/results of the response). This is a repeatable stage as multiple public health responses for the same foci can occur depending on its classification at the time of investigation.

programStages.name: Household investigation
programStages.description: Nearby household investigations occur when an index case is identified within a specific geographical area.

programStages.name: Inpatient morbidity and mortality
programStages.description: Anonymous and ICD-10 coded inpatient data

programStages.name: Postpartum care visit
programStages.description: Provision of care for the mother for some weeks after delivery
